[3] Saudi Arabia, 4 new cases, 3 fatalities - MOH 30 May 2015, RFI
Date: 30 May 2015
Source: Saudi MOH 30 May 2015 [edited]
http://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CCC/PressReleases/Pages/Statistics-2015-05-30-001.aspx


As of 12 noon today, 30 May 2015 there have been a total of:
1014 laboratory confirmed cases of MERS-CoV infection including
445 deaths
561 recoveries and
8 cases currently active including 1 case on home isolation.

In the past 24 hours there have been
4 newly confirmed cases and
3 newly reported fatalities

Information on newly confirmed cases (4 cases):
1- Hufoof: 57-year-old Saudi female, non-healthcare worker, currently in stable condition, history of contact with other case(s) in either healthcare environment or in the community.

2- Hufoof: 48-year-old Saudi male, non-healthcare worker, currently in stable condition, history of contact with other case(s) in either healthcare environment or in the community.

3- Hufoof: 50-year-old Saudi female, non-healthcare worker, reported as a fatality at time of initial confirmation report, history of contact with other case(s) in either the healthcare environment or in the community.

4- Hufoof: 43-year-old Saudi male, non-healthcare worker, currently in critical condition, history of contact with other case(s) in either the healthcare environment or in the community.

Information on newly reported deaths (3 fatalities):

1- Hufoof: 70-year-old Saudi male non-healthcare worker, history of pre-existing co-morbidities [reported as a newly confirmed case on 29 May 2015 at which time was noted to be in critical condition. At time of initial report was noted to have had contact with other case(s) in either the healthcare environment or in the community. - Mod.MPP]

2- Taif: 65-year-old Saudi male, non-healthcare worker, history of pre-existing co-morbidities [reported as a newly confirmed case on 26 May 2015 at which time was noted to be in critical condition in the ICU. At the time of the initial report possible contact with other case(s) in either the healthcare environment or in the community was under review. - Mod.MPP]

3- Hufoof: 50-year-old Saudi female, non-healthcare worker, history of pre-existing co-morbidities [at time of initial confirmation report today, 30 May 2015 patient was reported as a fatality. In addition, patient was noted to have had contact with other case(s) in either the healthcare environment or in the community. - Mod.MPP]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Cases are continuing to occur in Saudi Arabia, and during the past 3 days there have been 8 newly confirmed cases reported, with 7 of the 8 reported from Hufoof. According to social media reports, it appears as though the current outbreak ongoing in Hufoof is a hospital-based outbreak, as well as having involved a large extended family household in the early stages. Since the 1st case in this current outbreak was reported on 20 Apr 2015, there have been a total of 18 cases reported from Hufoof, of which 12 gave a history of contact with other case(s) in either the healthcare environment or in the community. It will be interesting to see results of epidemiologic studies identifying the chains of transmission that have led to the 18 cases. It would also be of interest to know how many of the cases were household contacts vs in-hospital contacts. Might one of our readers have detailed information on this that can be shared?

Of note is that the 1st "large" healthcare-associated outbreak in Saudi Arabia occurred in Al Hasa province, of which Hufoof is the capital city. (see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Al-Ahsa_Governorate#Main_cities for details). Is there yet another hospital-based outbreak in the same province? If so, what is different about this current outbreak from the earlier outbreak that has led to hospital-based transmission?

A map showing the location of Hufoof in Saudi Arabia can be found at today's source URL. - Mod.MPP]

